        "comment": {
            "comments": [
                {
                    "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/issue/13421993/comment/17472832",
                    "id": "17472832",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=39937",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=39937",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=39937",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=39937"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Nicola Crane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Africa/Casablanca"
                    },
                    "body": "I don't find them too bad, but given I wrote a load of extra documentation for some of the functions as I just couldn't understand the whole lot in the first place, I'm probably not the best person to ask here ;) \u00a0\r\n\r\nOne thing I'll say is that I don't think there's necessarily a need to know about all the custom expectations until you need to use them, and can do so by analogy; I'm a committer and have written a fair few bindings but am unaware of at least half of those custom expectations as I've never needed them.\r\n\r\nAll that said, *if* there's no negative consequences of doing so, I don't see the harm in reorganising things here though, and am in favour of things that'll make life easier for new contributors regardless.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=thisisnic",
                        "name": "thisisnic",
                        "key": "thisisnic",
                        "avatarUrls": {
